**AsmetaV** (Asmeta Validator) can be used to validate AsmetaL specifications by scenarios.

### Installation 

The validator can be used either embedded in eclipse or as standalone program. For the eclipse version, follow the instructions [here](./index.html#installing-asmeta-in-eclipse)

### Use in eclipse
<p>You can run the tool in two modes:</p>
<ul>
  <li><img src="https://github.com/asmeta/asmeta/raw/master/code/extensions/asmeta.validator/asmeta.validator.ui/icons/runValidator.gif"/> executes the scenario</li>
  <li><img src="https://github.com/asmeta/asmeta/raw/master/code/extensions/asmeta.validator/asmeta.validator.ui/icons/runValidatorAndCoverage.gif"/> executes the scenario and computes the coverage</li>
</ul>

### Download as standalone
<p>Download the validator: <a
 href="http://svn.code.sf.net/p/asmeta/code/code/stable/validator/asmeta.validator.cli/AsmetaV.jar">
AsmetaV.jar</a></p>
<h3>How to run<br/>
</h3>
To run the ASM <span style="font-weight: bold;">validator - in brief</span>
<pre>java -jar AsmetaV.jar &lt;filename&gt;</pre>

